children.subject: btw the 6.5 hours includes lecture time for both classes (as lectures were recorded)

The average person will take a little more time per week than 6.5 hours for EE 120 (the lectures themselves are 4 hours, and the homework/lab will probably take longer than 2.5 hours for most people, and discussions are also useful to attend). I'd say it's still far less work than EE 16AB, and a little less than EECS 126 - I'd probably peg the workload at around 10-12 hours per week.

To give you some context, I spent the same amount of time on EE 120 and EE 127 over the same semester (6.5 hours per week). 
I got a comfortable A in 120 and got an A- in 127 (tho very close to an A)

I think it definitely depends a bit on your background, but I'd agree with Anon Atom that EE120 is lower workload than 126 and maybe around 10-12 hours a week. 229A seems professor-dependent, but for last fall's iteration with Prof Ramchandran, I'd put it at around the same or a little bit more work than EE126.
